<div1 type="envelope">

<pb facs="nei.j4b.11b.5.001" />
<fw type="curatorial"></fw>
<note type="curatorial">Fink Collection 
51></note>

<ab type="postmark">OZARK JUN16 10-1935 THIS SIDE OF CARD IS FOR ADDRESS</ab>

<figure type="stamp"><ab>UNITEDSTATESPOSTAGE ONECENT 1WASHINGTON1</ab></figure>

<ab type="return">
<address>
<addrLine>The Misses Neihardt </addrLine>
<addrLine>Branson 
Mo</addrLine>
</address>
</ab>
</div1>

<div1 type="letter">
<fw>Ozark</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>
</dateline>
<salute>Dearest children</salute>
</opener>

<p>including Max we are sitting in the window of the Ozark Cafe waiting for "Hot Cakes" and coffee - It quit rain-ing at 8 o'clock and the Sun peep ed through the clouds at us! The car is running perfectly and we are all three as happy as can be - I'll never forget the sight of you 4 darlings like birdies in a nest calling out to us as we left. Mama is very rich and very fortunate and she loves you a lot</p>

<closer>
<salute></salute>
<signed>Mother </signed>
<note></note>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

